# Intuition
The chosen integers have to be in the range `[1, N]`, this led me to think about using Cycle Sort.

# Approach
Use Cycle Sort to sort the banned array.
If the banned array has less elements than `[1, N]`, we resize the array to make the indices be of the form `[0, N-1]`. (Cycle Sort relies on the indices for sorting)

While resizing the banned array, initialize the element to a number outside the 
range `[1, N]` so chose -1.

Then apply Cycle Sort to place the elements [1, N] in their correct positions.
For example:
The `0th index contains 1` (if 1 is present in the banned array).
The `kth index contains (k+1)`.

After sorting, iterate through the banned array.
If `banned[i] != (i+1)` that means the number `i+1` can be considered. And since we need to maximize the count the lower elements are to be considered from [1, N].
After selecting a number decrement it from `maxSum` and increment the `count`. When `maxSum < 0` break and return the count.

> Note:
Cycle Sort is a pre-requisite.
The given Banned array is modified. [Drawback of using Cycle Sort]
The resizing must be done only if the banned array indices do not fall between [0, N-1].


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(N)$$

- Space complexity:
If resize required, $$O(N)$$. Otherwise $$O(1)$$

# Code
## C++
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxCount(vector<int>& banned, int n, int maxSum) {
        // Ensure banned array has enough elements
        if(n > banned.size()) {
            banned.resize(n, -1); // Resize and initialize with -1
        }

        // Cycle Sort to sort the banned array
        for(int i=0; i<banned.size(); ) {
            if(banned[i]<=banned.size() && banned[i]!=banned[banned[i]-1]) {
                swap(banned[i], banned[banned[i]-1]);
            } else {
                i++;
            }
        }

        int count = 0;
        // Iterate through the search space [1, N]
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) {
            if(banned[i] != (i+1)) {
                maxSum -= (i+1);
                if(maxSum >= 0) count++;
                else {
                    break; // No need to continue, we can't add more elements
                }
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
};
```
